WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.798 --> 00:00:10.218
<i>Are athletes born athletes?</i>

2
00:00:11.219 --> 00:00:13.763
<i>What about astronauts or pop stars?</i>

3
00:00:15.306 --> 00:00:17.308
<i>No one knows at birth.</i>

4
00:00:18.560 --> 00:00:21.563
<i>But then. what about witches?</i>

5
00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:29.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

6
00:01:23.083 --> 00:01:24.542
Sorry for getting it dirty.

7
00:01:25.043 --> 00:01:26.669
I'm almost done washing.

8
00:01:30.340 --> 00:01:32.258
{\an8}It'll turn right back to normal.

9
00:01:32.342 --> 00:01:35.428
{\an8}This spring is under a spell!

10
00:01:59.661 --> 00:02:01.913
It never gets old. It's so beautiful.

11
00:02:01.996 --> 00:02:04.582
{\an8}Magic is amazing!

12
00:02:08.169 --> 00:02:10.588
<i>The world is brimming with magic.</i>

13
00:02:11.131 --> 00:02:13.967
<i>It's a practical miracle</i>
<i>we can't live without.</i>

14
00:02:16.094 --> 00:02:18.429
{\an8}<i>But we don't know how it works.</i>

15
00:02:18.513 --> 00:02:19.848
{\an8}THE MAGIC OF BEGINNINGS

16
00:02:19.931 --> 00:02:23.351
{\an8}<i>Only witches can cast spells.</i>

17
00:02:25.061 --> 00:02:29.190
<i>Ordinary people can only receive magic.</i>

18
00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:32.485
<i>We can never become witches.</i>

19
00:02:35.613 --> 00:02:38.867
Those born witches are so lucky.

20
00:02:46.583 --> 00:02:51.796
Oh. sheet. my sheet…
turn into a flying cloak!

21
00:02:56.092 --> 00:02:57.177
Oh no!

22
00:02:57.260 --> 00:03:00.305
Wait! No!
That's not what I meant by flying!

23
00:03:17.071 --> 00:03:18.198
It's a pegasus carriage!

24
00:03:31.836 --> 00:03:34.505
It's my first time seeing one land!

25
00:03:37.050 --> 00:03:40.386
Mom! There's a pegasus carriage outside!

26
00:03:41.429 --> 00:03:42.764
Mom!

27
00:03:44.265 --> 00:03:46.351
Mom!

28
00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:55.777
I'm sorry! I didn't see you.

29
00:03:56.361 --> 00:03:59.739
It's okay. My fault for standing
in front of the door.

30
00:03:59.822 --> 00:04:01.699
Oh. I can't believe this!

31
00:04:01.783 --> 00:04:04.702
Look at this!
I can't believe they have this here.

32
00:04:04.786 --> 00:04:08.122
Oh. but don't you think
the oxalis embroidery is outdated?

33
00:04:08.206 --> 00:04:11.417
More importantly. look!
This is Harian-knit lace!

34
00:04:11.501 --> 00:04:12.585
That's amazing!

35
00:04:12.669 --> 00:04:15.338
It sold out instantly in the castle town.

36
00:04:16.506 --> 00:04:19.759
Those customers must have come
on a pegasus carriage!

37
00:04:21.511 --> 00:04:23.054
Oh. no. not me.

38
00:04:23.638 --> 00:04:26.724
Excuse me. ma'am.
do you have more lace like this?

39
00:04:26.808 --> 00:04:28.768
Yes. right away!

40
00:04:29.560 --> 00:04:31.896
Coco. help me out if you're here.

41
00:04:33.273 --> 00:04:35.024
What would you like. sir?

42
00:04:35.108 --> 00:04:38.778
I'd like some smoke-colored fabric.
but if you're busy. I can wait.

43
00:04:38.861 --> 00:04:40.780
I can measure it out for you.

44
00:04:40.863 --> 00:04:41.781
You can?

45
00:04:41.864 --> 00:04:43.741
Coco is quite good.

46
00:04:43.825 --> 00:04:44.659
Is that so?

47
00:04:47.829 --> 00:04:50.873
Hey. can I go see
the pegasus carriage when I'm done?

48
00:04:50.957 --> 00:04:52.208
What?

49
00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:53.626
A pegasus carriage is here!

50
00:04:54.335 --> 00:04:55.461
A pegasus carriage?

51
00:04:55.545 --> 00:04:58.506
You're not going to play with
customer property. are you?

52
00:04:58.589 --> 00:05:00.341
Don't worry. I'll just look!

53
00:05:02.802 --> 00:05:06.347
I'll stop saying I want to be a witch.

54
00:05:10.601 --> 00:05:12.520
Only if you finish your work early.

55
00:05:13.062 --> 00:05:14.480
Yes!

56
00:05:15.606 --> 00:05:18.151
Thank you for waiting!
How much would you like?

57
00:05:18.234 --> 00:05:19.360
Oh. here.

58
00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:20.570
I'll take care of it.

59
00:06:00.943 --> 00:06:01.861
Wow.

60
00:06:03.529 --> 00:06:05.323
That's quite the focus.

61
00:06:05.406 --> 00:06:06.741
Steady hands too.

62
00:06:06.824 --> 00:06:09.869
Clean lines and decisive cuts.

63
00:06:09.952 --> 00:06:12.789
And most of all.
your finish is so careful and exact.

64
00:06:13.539 --> 00:06:16.542
I had no idea
this village had such a wonderful artisan.

65
00:06:18.211 --> 00:06:19.504
<i>This </i>is magic.

66
00:06:20.963 --> 00:06:25.385
No! My work is nothing like that!

67
00:06:25.468 --> 00:06:28.388
Magic is something more mysterious.
more sparkly.

68
00:06:28.471 --> 00:06:30.390
more precious. and beautiful.

69
00:06:30.473 --> 00:06:32.100
And it's more…

70
00:06:32.850 --> 00:06:33.684
it's more…

71
00:06:34.185 --> 00:06:37.522
it's more… sacred.

72
00:06:38.189 --> 00:06:40.400
What am I even saying?

73
00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:43.069
You really love magic. don't you?

74
00:06:45.696 --> 00:06:47.573
May I ask you why?

75
00:06:53.454 --> 00:06:57.583
<i>When I was little.</i>
<i>I was taken to a festival at the castle.</i>

76
00:06:58.126 --> 00:07:00.837
<i>I met a witch wearing a mask there.</i>

77
00:07:19.021 --> 00:07:20.481
You there.

78
00:07:22.191 --> 00:07:24.819
Would you like to buy a picture book
about magic?

79
00:07:27.447 --> 00:07:32.493
Magic? I like picture books.
but what's magic?

80
00:07:33.077 --> 00:07:37.081
Magic is a miracle
that brings color to the world.

81
00:07:38.749 --> 00:07:41.169
The pegasus carriages
that soar across the sky.

82
00:07:41.252 --> 00:07:44.130
and the eternal springs
that keep their water pure.

83
00:07:44.213 --> 00:07:49.677
And even the cobblestones that glow
when you step on them.

84
00:07:49.760 --> 00:07:51.762
All of it is magic.

85
00:07:54.056 --> 00:07:55.641
This is so pretty!

86
00:07:55.725 --> 00:07:59.604
Magic is so amazing! I love magic!

87
00:08:00.104 --> 00:08:02.398
Now with a free wand included!

88
00:08:05.985 --> 00:08:08.654
So you were tricked into buying that?

89
00:08:09.238 --> 00:08:11.699
You said you wanted to eat
grilled strawberries.

90
00:08:11.782 --> 00:08:16.287
Well. I was chasing a butterfly.
and then I met a person with a pointy hat.

91
00:08:16.370 --> 00:08:18.331
You already told me that.

92
00:08:18.414 --> 00:08:22.668
So it's a picture book about magic!
And a free wand!

93
00:08:25.171 --> 00:08:28.549
Okay. Coco. it's time to go home.
It's getting late.

94
00:08:28.633 --> 00:08:29.592
Mom!

95
00:08:30.259 --> 00:08:35.932
When I grow up. I'm going to be a witch
who brings color to the world!

96
00:08:36.015 --> 00:08:37.266
That's impossible.

97
00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:38.601
Why is that?!

98
00:08:41.062 --> 00:08:46.359
You can't become a witch unless
you were born with the power of magic.

99
00:08:46.901 --> 00:08:50.780
Ordinary people don't have
the innate ability to become witches.

100
00:08:52.657 --> 00:08:54.492
Now. Coco. Let's go home.

101
00:08:54.575 --> 00:08:55.701
But look!

102
00:08:55.785 --> 00:08:58.704
The path glows when I step on it.

103
00:09:01.666 --> 00:09:06.170
Then. if it keeps glowing
all the way home.

104
00:09:06.921 --> 00:09:09.090
maybe you can use magic too.

105
00:09:18.683 --> 00:09:23.396
Since then. I just like looking at it.
Or maybe I just can't let it go.

106
00:09:23.980 --> 00:09:26.190
Can you tell me more about what--

107
00:09:27.984 --> 00:09:29.318
What was that?

108
00:09:30.987 --> 00:09:33.364
Hey. stop it. Stay still.

109
00:09:34.407 --> 00:09:35.533
Easy. easy.

110
00:09:45.376 --> 00:09:47.503
What are you doing? Jeez.

111
00:09:47.587 --> 00:09:49.505
Shut up. Ow…

112
00:09:49.589 --> 00:09:50.631
Are you okay?

113
00:09:51.549 --> 00:09:52.717
What happened?

114
00:09:53.217 --> 00:09:55.177
I didn't do anything. It just broke.

115
00:09:55.261 --> 00:09:58.389
Huh? That's not true.
Tanerl went under it!

116
00:09:58.472 --> 00:09:59.849
Tattle-tale!

117
00:09:59.932 --> 00:10:02.393
He hit his head on the bottom.
and it flipped over.

118
00:10:02.476 --> 00:10:04.437
Oh my! What in the world?

119
00:10:05.229 --> 00:10:06.981
Our pegasus carriage…

120
00:10:07.064 --> 00:10:09.233
We borrowed it from Father too.

121
00:10:09.317 --> 00:10:12.987
Please accept my apologies.
The village children behaved terribly.

122
00:10:13.070 --> 00:10:15.281
An apology won't help.

123
00:10:15.364 --> 00:10:17.366
We can't go home without the carriage!

124
00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:19.243
I don't know what more to say.

125
00:10:20.536 --> 00:10:21.412
Pardon me.

126
00:10:23.789 --> 00:10:25.166
Would you like me to fix it?

127
00:10:27.043 --> 00:10:29.920
It doesn't look like
the damage is that bad.

128
00:10:30.004 --> 00:10:32.173
Excuse me. but who are you?

129
00:10:32.256 --> 00:10:35.885
My apologies. I forgot my signature item.

130
00:10:42.016 --> 00:10:45.436
Qifrey the witch. at your service.

131
00:10:48.397 --> 00:10:50.191
- A pointed hat.
- A pointed hat.

132
00:10:50.858 --> 00:10:51.942
You can fix it?

133
00:10:52.026 --> 00:10:52.860
Yes.

134
00:10:53.402 --> 00:10:55.863
Thank you. Mr. Witch.

135
00:10:55.946 --> 00:10:56.906
It'll be all right.

136
00:10:57.657 --> 00:11:00.451
I just have to recast the spell
on the bottom of the carriage.

137
00:11:00.534 --> 00:11:02.328
I'd love for you to do it.

138
00:11:02.828 --> 00:11:04.288
Please leave it to me.

139
00:11:04.372 --> 00:11:06.582
But I can't really do it outside.

140
00:11:06.666 --> 00:11:08.751
You can use our workshop!

141
00:11:10.127 --> 00:11:11.545
It's okay. right. Mom?

142
00:11:13.214 --> 00:11:14.048
<i>I mean.</i>

143
00:11:14.882 --> 00:11:17.051
<i>he's a real witch.</i>

144
00:11:18.260 --> 00:11:20.888
<i>I might even get to see it.</i>

145
00:11:21.889 --> 00:11:24.725
<i>The moment he casts a spell.</i>

146
00:11:33.693 --> 00:11:35.444
While I'm casting the spell.

147
00:11:35.528 --> 00:11:39.073
I'd like you to keep watch outside
so no one peeks inside.

148
00:11:39.699 --> 00:11:43.160
Don't let anyone in. no matter what.
Got it?

149
00:11:46.288 --> 00:11:48.708
Life isn't that easy. I guess.

150
00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:52.712
<i>But I wonder why I can't watch.</i>

151
00:11:53.754 --> 00:11:57.091
<i>There is so much magic in the world.</i>

152
00:11:57.174 --> 00:11:59.969
<i>but we don't know how to cast it.</i>

153
00:12:00.553 --> 00:12:02.596
<i>Only witches know…</i>

154
00:12:03.431 --> 00:12:04.682
the secret.

155
00:12:11.188 --> 00:12:12.189
Huh?

156
00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:13.858
Whoa. it's slippery.

157
00:12:15.818 --> 00:12:17.570
Hey! What are you doing?

158
00:12:17.653 --> 00:12:18.571
Busted!

159
00:12:18.654 --> 00:12:20.239
It's just her. It’ll be fine.

160
00:12:20.322 --> 00:12:22.366
Can we peek in from here?

161
00:12:23.325 --> 00:12:24.326
Wait!

162
00:12:24.410 --> 00:12:25.995
Keep your voice down!

163
00:12:26.078 --> 00:12:27.079
Out of the way!

164
00:12:40.050 --> 00:12:41.969
Seriously? Lame.

165
00:12:42.052 --> 00:12:43.429
For real.

166
00:12:51.562 --> 00:12:52.396
What?

167
00:13:23.636 --> 00:13:25.387
<i>No. I can't.</i>

168
00:13:25.471 --> 00:13:28.057
<i>But I really want to see. But I shouldn't.</i>

169
00:13:55.918 --> 00:13:57.211
<i>He's drawing...</i>

170
00:14:01.423 --> 00:14:04.176
<i>magic... with a pen?!</i>

171
00:14:06.345 --> 00:14:07.721
Then that means...

172
00:14:08.931 --> 00:14:10.266
<i>it isn't a wand!</i>

173
00:14:12.101 --> 00:14:12.977
<i>Magic is</i>

174
00:14:14.603 --> 00:14:16.021
<i>not something you cast.</i>

175
00:14:17.982 --> 00:14:19.233
<i>It's something you draw!</i>

176
00:14:20.776 --> 00:14:21.986
Now. then.

177
00:14:22.778 --> 00:14:24.029
I'm done.

178
00:14:33.038 --> 00:14:34.623
Good job.

179
00:14:53.225 --> 00:14:55.561
I'm a bit relieved.

180
00:14:56.562 --> 00:14:59.064
With you loving magic so much.

181
00:14:59.607 --> 00:15:05.195
I thought that maybe you would say
you wanted to go with the witch.

182
00:15:07.239 --> 00:15:09.491
I already lost your father to illness.

183
00:15:10.034 --> 00:15:13.996
If you left too. I'd...

184
00:15:14.079 --> 00:15:17.875
I'd never say that!
I couldn't leave you all by yourself.

185
00:15:21.337 --> 00:15:25.174
Thank you. You're such a sweet girl. Coco.

186
00:15:43.442 --> 00:15:44.526
Good night.

187
00:15:44.610 --> 00:15:46.070
Good night.

188
00:15:50.824 --> 00:15:53.160
It's nothing. Good night.

189
00:15:54.078 --> 00:15:55.079
Good night.

190
00:16:03.754 --> 00:16:06.924
…you would say
you wanted to go with the witch.

191
00:16:24.692 --> 00:16:27.403
<i>All the patterns</i>
<i>drawn in the picture book…</i>

192
00:16:28.112 --> 00:16:31.240
<i>The magic wand wasn't just a freebie.</i>

193
00:16:32.366 --> 00:16:35.285
<i>The pen itself was the magic wand!</i>

194
00:16:49.049 --> 00:16:52.636
<i>I'm sorry. Mom. I won't go anywhere.</i>

195
00:16:53.178 --> 00:16:54.430
<i>But let me try.</i>

196
00:17:44.229 --> 00:17:45.064
Huh?

197
00:17:47.733 --> 00:17:50.194
Oh. it didn't work.

198
00:17:50.277 --> 00:17:53.405
Figures. I knew it couldn't be that easy.

199
00:18:19.973 --> 00:18:22.559
It glowed! I just used magic!

200
00:18:22.643 --> 00:18:26.897
Amazing! It's magic! It's magic!
It's real magic! What should I do?!

201
00:18:28.107 --> 00:18:29.733
So it <i>is </i>drawn.

202
00:18:29.817 --> 00:18:32.277
But I wasn't supposed to look.
Will I get in trouble?

203
00:18:37.699 --> 00:18:40.744
But just one more time.
Just one more page.

204
00:18:54.550 --> 00:18:57.219
<i>A picture book. A picture book. huh?</i>

205
00:18:59.054 --> 00:19:01.223
<i>I can't get it out of my mind.</i>

206
00:19:04.143 --> 00:19:05.060
Surely not?!

207
00:19:08.147 --> 00:19:11.150
That one was a fire spell!
No. no! Don't burn!

208
00:19:13.443 --> 00:19:14.486
That was close!

209
00:19:15.904 --> 00:19:16.738
But...

210
00:19:18.740 --> 00:19:20.742
I feel like I'm getting the hang of this.

211
00:19:21.368 --> 00:19:24.496
The bigger ones are stronger
than the smaller ones.

212
00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:27.833
and the ones I drew neatly
last longer than the messy ones!

213
00:19:28.834 --> 00:19:31.712
It's hard to draw them big and neatly.

214
00:19:32.254 --> 00:19:34.131
Qifrey drew them so easily.

215
00:19:34.882 --> 00:19:35.757
Oh. that's it!

216
00:19:41.346 --> 00:19:42.764
{\an8}<i>Just as I thought.</i>

217
00:19:42.848 --> 00:19:46.518
{\an8}<i>If I trace over the pattern.</i>
<i>I can draw them neatly!</i>

218
00:19:56.153 --> 00:19:57.154
I did it!

219
00:20:18.175 --> 00:20:19.051
You drew something.

220
00:20:19.134 --> 00:20:22.179
What did you draw?
What magic did you draw?!

221
00:20:22.262 --> 00:20:25.766
I don't know! I just traced the pattern
from the picture book!

222
00:20:29.770 --> 00:20:30.604
Mom!

223
00:20:36.693 --> 00:20:37.527
Run!

224
00:20:43.867 --> 00:20:45.786
No. That can't be...

225
00:20:46.662 --> 00:20:48.789
Mom! Mom!

226
00:20:48.872 --> 00:20:50.165
Mom!

227
00:20:50.249 --> 00:20:52.042
<i>This is forbidden magic--</i>

228
00:20:52.125 --> 00:20:53.293
No! Let me go!

229
00:20:53.377 --> 00:20:55.420
You'll get caught up in it too--

230
00:20:55.504 --> 00:20:56.797
I have to save my mom!

231
00:20:56.880 --> 00:20:59.883
It's no use! This is magic! And it's bad--

232
00:20:59.967 --> 00:21:00.801
Oh no!

233
00:21:06.974 --> 00:21:08.642
Mom!

234
00:21:10.227 --> 00:21:11.979
No!

235
00:21:16.942 --> 00:21:17.859
I'm sorry!

236
00:21:18.819 --> 00:21:20.153
I didn't know.

237
00:21:20.862 --> 00:21:22.656
Of course you didn't.

238
00:21:23.282 --> 00:21:25.659
It's kept secret
to prevent things like this.

239
00:21:26.702 --> 00:21:30.122
Special ink. prescribed seals.

240
00:21:30.205 --> 00:21:33.041
With those. anyone can use magic.

241
00:21:33.125 --> 00:21:35.669
It's the absolute secret of witches.

242
00:21:36.628 --> 00:21:40.173
{\an8}And now that you know.
I have to erase your memories.

243
00:21:44.177 --> 00:21:49.057
{\an8}No! If my memories are erased.
then who will save Mom?!

244
00:21:49.933 --> 00:21:51.560
I'm sorry. but...

245
00:21:52.269 --> 00:21:54.354
I don't remember the magic I drew.

246
00:21:54.438 --> 00:21:56.773
but I can recite the contents
of the picture book by heart!

247
00:21:57.274 --> 00:21:59.776
If I forget that. then my mom...

248
00:22:01.111 --> 00:22:02.070
The picture book...

249
00:22:02.738 --> 00:22:04.114
<i>Of course!</i>

250
00:22:04.197 --> 00:22:08.118
<i>If that book belongs to them.</i>
<i>I won't be able to track them.</i>

251
00:22:08.785 --> 00:22:12.122
<i>If I erase her memories.</i>
<i>then the trail will go cold.</i>

252
00:22:12.998 --> 00:22:15.292
{\an8}So you remember what the book was like?

253
00:22:15.375 --> 00:22:16.209
{\an8}Yes.

254
00:22:16.710 --> 00:22:18.754
{\an8}And what page the seal was drawn on?

255
00:22:18.837 --> 00:22:19.838
{\an8}Yes... Yes.

256
00:22:22.215 --> 00:22:25.344
{\an8}If I find the same book.
then the seal will be in it.

257
00:22:28.055 --> 00:22:30.015
{\an8}If you know which seal it is.

258
00:22:30.098 --> 00:22:31.892
{\an8}would you be able to save my mother?

259
00:22:34.936 --> 00:22:37.981
I might... be able to.

260
00:22:38.648 --> 00:22:39.733
Mr. Qifrey!

261
00:22:40.942 --> 00:22:43.070
Please. don't erase my memories!

262
00:22:43.153 --> 00:22:46.323
I'll do anything
if it means I can save my mother!

263
00:22:48.533 --> 00:22:49.910
Can you keep the secret?

264
00:22:50.410 --> 00:22:51.536
I promise!

265
00:22:53.038 --> 00:22:54.790
{\an8}Do you have the will to learn?

266
00:22:54.873 --> 00:22:55.874
{\an8}Learn…

267
00:22:57.417 --> 00:22:59.878
{\an8}If you are to retain the truth
you've learned.

268
00:23:00.379 --> 00:23:03.382
{\an8}then you'll have to stand alongside
us who keep the secret.

269
00:23:04.508 --> 00:23:07.761
{\an8}This is the only option
to keep your memories intact!

270
00:23:10.514 --> 00:23:11.640
From now on...

271
00:23:13.642 --> 00:23:15.560
you will become a witch.

272
00:23:33.620 --> 00:23:35.914
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Emily Noguchi

273
